{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Getting-the-URL-to-your-apps-System-Settings-screen","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Getting the URL to your app’s System Settings screen"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit has a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardSettingsUrlProvider"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol that provides any type that implements it with a static "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".keyboardSettings"},{"type":"text","text":" URL that leads to your app’s System Settings screen."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let url: URL = .keyboardSettings"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This protocol is implemented by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"URL"},{"type":"text","text":", which means that you can use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"URL.keyboardSettings"},{"type":"text","text":" to get the URL."}]},{"anchor":"Keyboard-settings-link","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Keyboard settings link"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit also has a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/KeyboardKit\/documentation\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardSettingsLink"},{"type":"text","text":" that will navigate the user to the settings url when tapped."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The link supports using a custom title, image and even url, although it will by default use values that make sense."}]},{"anchor":"Random-behavior","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Random behavior"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you have used the url above, you may have noticed that it sometimes leads to your app’s System Settings screen, as expected, while at other times it just takes you to the System Settings root."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This random behavior 